now let say that we plug the cortex to the spinal chord where are the cerrebelar outputs. Then we train the Cerrebelum/spinal chord neurons through two dynamics which takes place AT THE SAME TIME. On one side we train the spinal chord neurons to read the DCN output to reproduce the right cortex output. The spinal chord read the DCN the right way. At the same time we train the cerrebellum to cancel whatever IO activity there is using backpropagation. We will also make the spinal chord learning slower than the cerebellar learning through backprop.
This will induce interferences as the DCN code will change during the time the spinal chord learn. But these interferences inducing kind of random mouvement but not really wont hinder the Cerebellum to map itself through backpropagation. Even better the more the mouvements are random, the more the cerrebellum can learn to map the IO in various situations and therefor we will see the DCN code stabilize even if the behavior is not the right one, as the cerebellum learns an agnostic predictive model of its internal activity. 

Ok now we are at equilibrium, the whole system is able to output the right behavior from the cerrebellum output. Fine we have found an overcomplicated way to make what the cortex was able to do alone. But here is where magic happens (maybe).
Let say now we operate in a regime where the cortex is frozen AND spinal chord learning is frozen. lets also froze the cerrebellum learning in this first scenario to only observe what I coined the target alignement phenomenon.

Let's imagine a scenario whereby the cortex drive alone the ball most of the time until the target. then for fractions of seconds we unplug the cortex and only listen the cerrebellum imitating a period during which the cortex gives the wrong output (or no output). This could be because of lag or bad processing. (this scenario is not really realistic but it is a simplify setup. In the more sophisticated setup we will make the cortex outputting the wrong output and deal with the spinal chord activity such that the cerrebellum stear the behavior by compensating for the gap between good and wrong behavor). So yes the cortex is unplugged on for a fraction of second we only listen the cerrebellum. what I predict will happen is that the cerrebellum will be able to do what I call high dimensional dead reconning. By just reading the high dimensional activity comming from sensory/motor/proprioceptive and generating the right code for the IO to be inhibited, the cerrebellum will output the right code and the spinal chord will read from it the right way to produce during this short period of time the right behavior. This is also a form of interpolation if we think about it.
So yes this is the first big part.

Now for the gradient aligment phenomenon. It is a bit more subtile and has to do with cerrebellar on the fly rather fast plasticity. Here the cerrebellum not only predict the right code but the right code change, the right gradient.
